    "Second, defining normative thresholds is extremely difficult: What level of risk is acceptable?",
    "How fair is fair enough?",
    "Third, in many cases, AI companies are detached from the people who are most affected by their systems, often historically marginalized communities [26,103].",
    "Fourth, risk assessments might become even more difficult in the future.",
    "For example, systems might become capable of deceiving their operators and only \"pretending\" to be safe in a testing environment [116,132].The ethics board could actively contribute to the different steps of a risk assessment."
